                            <comment id="12586744" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Tue, 8 Apr 2008 10:31:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just noticed another problem: the contructor uses the length of the field _lineSeparatorBytes &lt;b&gt;before&lt;/b&gt; assigning to it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it&apos;s highly unlikely that the line separator value will ever require different bytes in different encodings.&lt;br/&gt;
However, if it does, then using a static field is not the correct way to communicate the value to the FromNetASCIIOutputStream class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12586874" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Tue, 8 Apr 2008 16:36:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Does not apply to 1.5&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12586878" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Tue, 8 Apr 2008 16:45:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reverted the code back to the way that 1.5 does it.&lt;/p&gt;

